{"action":"created","comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments/1805389330","pull_request_review_id":2376224888,"id":1805389330,"node_id":"PRRC_kwDOABkWpM5rnA4S","diff_hunk":"@@ -184,7 +185,93 @@ JL_DLLEXPORT int jl_profile_is_buffer_full(void)
     // Declare buffer full if there isn't enough room to sample even just the
     // thread metadata and one max-sized frame. The `+ 6` is for the two block
     // terminator `0`'s plus the 4 metadata entries.
-    return bt_size_cur + ((JL_BT_MAX_ENTRY_SIZE + 1) + 6) > bt_size_max;
+    return profile_bt_size_cur + ((JL_BT_MAX_ENTRY_SIZE + 1) + 6) > profile_bt_size_max;
+}
+
+void jl_profile_task(void)
+{
+    if (jl_profile_is_buffer_full()) {
+        // Buffer full: Delete the timer
+        jl_profile_stop_timer();
+        return;
+    }
+
+    arraylist_t *tasks = jl_get_all_tasks_arraylist();
+    jl_task_t *t = NULL;
+    uint64_t seed = jl_rand();
+
+    const int n_max_random_attempts = (1 << 16);
+    // randomly select a task that is not done
+    for (int i = 0; i < n_max_random_attempts; i++) {
+        t = (jl_task_t*)tasks->items[cong(tasks->len, &seed)];
+        assert(t == NULL || jl_is_task(t));
+        if (t == NULL) {
+            continue;
+        }
+        int t_state = jl_atomic_load_relaxed(&t->_state);
+        if (t_state == JL_TASK_STATE_DONE) {
+            continue;
+        }
+        break;
+    }
+    // sequentially select a task that is not done
+    for (int i = 0; i < tasks->len; i++) {
+        t = (jl_task_t*)tasks->items[i];
+        assert(t == NULL || jl_is_task(t));
+        if (t == NULL) {
+            continue;
+        }
+        int t_state = jl_atomic_load_relaxed(&t->_state);
+        if (t_state == JL_TASK_STATE_DONE) {
+            continue;
+        }
+        break;
+    }
+    assert(t != NULL);
+
+    arraylist_free(tasks);
+    free(tasks);
+
+    jl_bt_element_t *bt_data_prof = (jl_bt_element_t*)(profile_bt_data_prof + profile_bt_size_cur);
+    size_t bt_size_max = profile_bt_size_max - profile_bt_size_cur - 1;
+
+    jl_record_backtrace_result_t r = jl_record_backtrace(t, bt_data_prof, bt_size_max, 1);
+
+    int tid = r.tid;
+    // we failed to get a backtrace
+    if (r.bt_size == 0) {
+        return;
+    }","path":"src/signal-handling.c","commit_id":"ebe4c17d7c291fc00f5333e615bc37644c79f936","original_commit_id":"ebe4c17d7c291fc00f5333e615bc37644c79f936","user":{"login":"nickrobinson251","id":13448787,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNDQ4Nzg3","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/13448787?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251","html_url":"https://github.com/nickrobinson251","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/nickrobinson251/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"body":"is it okay to just not record anything if we fail to get a backtrace? That changes the effective sample rate, which i think is going to affect downstream analysis of the results.

Also, do we have any data on how frequently this occurs / what it depends on?

Can the existing `@profile` ever fail to get a backtrace?

I think one option (maybe @NHDaly suggested this) is to consider adding some kind of "fake" backtrace that indicates "sample failed", so at least a failure to sample is present in the data.
I think another option (i think maybe the Go profilers do this?) is to somehow return to the user what the true sample rate was. 

Might be worth asking Todd's perspective on this.","created_at":"2024-10-17T20:28:29Z","updated_at":"2024-10-17T20:28:29Z","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55889#discussion_r1805389330","pull_request_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/55889","author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","_links":{"self":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments/1805389330"},"html":{"href":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55889#discussion_r1805389330"},"pull_request":{"href":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/55889"}},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/comments/1805389330/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"start_line":null,"original_start_line":null,"start_side":null,"line":244,"original_line":244,"side":"RIGHT","original_position":140,"position":140,"subject_type":"line"},"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/pulls/55889","id":2093832634,"node_id":"PR_kwDOABkWpM58zVm6","html_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55889","diff_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55889.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/pull/55889.patch","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/JuliaLang/julia/issues/55889","number":55889,"state":"open","locked":false,"title":"Wall-time/all tasks profiler","user":{"login":"d-netto","id":61364108,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjYxMzY0MTA4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/61364108?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/d-netto","html_url":"https://github.com/d-netto","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/d-netto/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/d-netto/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/d-netto/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/d-netto/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.c